    "difficulty": "high",
    "goal": "Make Windows and Python 3.10 regression execution deterministic without changing the production CLI contract.",
    "description": "Scope: Closure: scenario - Windows test portability across CLI subprocess helpers, architecture analysis, installer isolation, and CI. Context: the nightly suite exposed argument-ordering mistakes, a Python 3.11-only AST reference, and inherited host tool discovery. Target: all 204 tests pass on Windows Python 3.10 and CI preserves that coverage. Design Considerations: keep the strict CLI grammar, use version-aware AST node tuples, isolate PATH and WSL probes at test boundaries, and use a bounded OS/Python matrix. Design Value: failures represent repository behavior rather than the developer workstation. Constraints & Risks: no production parser fallback, no removal of optional-client runtime verification, no host CLI execution from tests, and no persistence of machine-specific output.",
    "requirements": [
      "REQ-WIN-001",
      "REQ-WIN-002",
      "REQ-WIN-003",
      "REQ-WIN-004"
    ],
